      634.01
    ],
    "text": "Aggrieved by this decision, the 2nd Accused filed a revision application to the High Court of Kegalle",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      8.039999961853027,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      641.37,
      558.15,
      654.65
    ],
    "text": "under Case No. H.C.R./5114/R. After listening to both parties at the inquiry, the learned High Court",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      661.1,
      398.83,
      675.41
    ],
    "text": "Judge held with the Magistrate by order dated 12th of December 2017.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      8.039999961853027,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      731.38,
      557.72,
      755.86
    ],
    "text": "Page 4 of 6",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      71.44,
      558.17,
      85.77
    ],
    "text": "The 2nd Accused, who is the Appellant of the present case, and other party parties filed their written",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      8.039999961853027,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      93.13,
      558.22,
      106.41
    ],
    "text": "submissions and held oral arguments in Court, and this judgment is in respect of those arguments. The",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      113.89,
      558.08,
      127.17
    ],
    "text": "Appellant and the Respondent placed arguments before this Court on the same arguments they had",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      134.53,
      334.39,
      147.81
    ],
    "text": "placed before the Magistrate's Court and the High Court.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      175.93,
      528.94,
      189.21
    ],
    "text": "The Appellant placed his arguments and stated that the Respondents had not followed the statute.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      217.33,
      365.95,
      230.61
    ],
    "text": "Section 23(1) of the Food Act No.26 of 1980 reads as follows:-",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      238.09,
      557.98,
      251.37
    ],
    "text": "\"In the absence of evidence to the contrary, a document purporting to be a report or a certificate signed",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      258.76,
      558.01,
      272.04
    ],
    "text": "by the approved Analyst or an additional approved Analyst upon any matter submitted to him for",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      279.52,
      447.55,
      292.8
    ],
    "text": "examination or analysis shall be sufficient evidence of the facts stated therein.\"",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      320.92,
      558.05,
      334.2
    ],
    "text": "It further states that such report or a certificate of the approved Analyst shall not be received in evidence",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      341.56,
      557.89,
      354.84
    ],
    "text": "by the learned Magistrate unless the prosecution has complied with the two conditions in Section 23(3)",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      362.32,
      140.66,
      375.6
    ],
    "text": "of the Food Act.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      403.72,
      192.86,
      417.0
    ],
    "text": "According to Section 23(3)",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      76.94,
      423.95,
      522.82,
      438.14
    ],
    "text": "- The prosecution should have furnished a copy of the report or certificate to the Accused.",
    "fonts": [
      "ArialMT",
      "LucidaFax",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.94,
      445.62,
      118.58,
      458.9
    ],
    "text": "And",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.94,
      466.26,
      558.15,
      479.54
    ],
    "text": "Reasonable notice of the intention of producing the report or certificate in the evidence must be",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.94,
      487.02,
      280.85,
      500.3
    ],
    "text": "communicated to the Accused person.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      528.42,
      558.13,
      541.7
    ],
    "text": "In the Magistrate's Court and the High Court, the judges were satisfied that the summons had given",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      549.06,
      455.35,
      562.34
    ],
    "text": "enough notice of the intention regarding marking the Analyst's report in evidence.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      590.49,
      557.92,
      603.77
    ],
    "text": "On behalf of the Appellant, it was argued that Section 24(2) of the Food Act had given an opportunity",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      611.25,
      558.21,
      624.53
    ],
    "text": "to the Accused person to challenge the report. Provision is made in the Act to request from Court to send",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      631.89,
      259.97,
      645.17
    ],
    "text": "the remaining sample to another Analyst.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      673.29,
      558.16,
      686.57
    ],
    "text": "According to the Food Act, when the prosecution requests a sample to be sent to the Analyst, it is",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      693.92,
      432.91,
      707.21
    ],
    "text": "mandatory for the Magistrate to send to the Analyst and retain the other .",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      731.38,
      557.72,
      755.86
    ],
    "text": "Page 5 of 6",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      93.13,
      558.07,
      106.41
    ],
    "text": "When perusing the Magistrate Court's case record, the Analyst examined the sample and made his report",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      112.86,
      558.2,
      127.17
    ],
    "text": "on the 5th day of 2015. This indicates that the report had come to Court within a short time. The",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      8.039999961853027,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      134.53,
      558.17,
      147.81
    ],
    "text": "prosecution pointed out that the time taken by the Analyst to report back was two months. However, for",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      154.26,
      374.23,
      168.57
    ],
    "text": "18 more months, the report was kept away from the 2nd Accused.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      8.039999961853027,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      196.69,
      558.2,
      209.97
    ],
    "text": "The prosecution argued that the accused was served a copy along with the charge sheet, therefor he was",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      217.33,
      558.17,
      230.61
    ],
    "text": "aware that the report would be marked in evidence. If the Accused was interested, he could have",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      238.09,
      558.08,
      251.37
    ],
    "text": "requested from Court to send the remaining sample to the Analyst. When the Appellant had not exercised",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      258.76,
      310.25,
      272.04
    ],
    "text": "his right, he cannot now seek relief from this Court.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      300.16,
      558.22,
      313.44
    ],
    "text": "To accept the prosecution's argument, they should satisfy that summons contained a copy of the report",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      320.92,
      558.16,
      334.2
    ],
    "text": "even though Section 44(3) of the Criminal Procedure Code stipulates that sending a copy of the Case",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      341.56,
      558.23,
      354.84
    ],
    "text": "record does not bear witness to sending a copy. The amended charge sheet holds the names of two",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      362.32,
      385.27,
      375.6
    ],
    "text": "witnesses and three documents named Idiripathkirima in Sinhalese.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      403.72,
      558.14,
      417.0
    ],
    "text": "An argument was formed by the prosecution that it is not late, even now, for the Appellant to request to",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      424.38,
      558.11,
      437.66
    ],
    "text": "send a sample. What he should have done on the day he objected to the marking of [P3] was to request",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      445.14,
      289.85,
      458.42
    ],
    "text": "from Court to send the other half to an Analyst.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      486.54,
      558.11,
      499.82
    ],
    "text": "As pointed out by the Appellant, after a delay of eighteen months, the sample will not hold the evidential",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      507.18,
      389.23,
      520.46
    ],
    "text": "value. Iodine will change due to sunlight and other external reasons.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      548.58,
      558.21,
      561.86
    ],
    "text": "For centuries, this country's criminal law principles held that let a hundred guilty go free rather than one",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      569.34,
      558.17,
      582.62
    ],
    "text": "innocent person is punished. This rule made judgers to be very careful when the Court exercises its",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      590.01,
      558.13,
      603.29
    ],
    "text": "powers in imposing punishments. The verdict should be pronounced not on a balance of probability but",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      610.77,
      193.22,
      624.05
    ],
    "text": "beyond a reasonable doubt.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      652.17,
      558.14,
      665.45
    ],
    "text": "When a person is handed over the charge sheet and evidence taken on the same day, there is no time to",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      672.81,
      354.67,
      686.09
    ],
    "text": "object or request from Court to send a sample to the Analyst.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      731.38,
      557.72,
      755.86
    ],
    "text": "Page 6 of 6",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      72.49,
      558.08,
      85.77
    ],
    "text": "According to the record, the amended charge sheet was read in Court and given to the 2nd Accused (The",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      93.13,
      558.17,
      106.41
    ],
    "text": "Appellant) on the 4th of January 2016. On that same day, P.W.1 had given evidence, and the prosecution",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      113.89,
      317.57,
      127.17
    ],
    "text": "had sought permission to mark the document as [P3].",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      155.29,
      558.22,
      168.57
    ],
    "text": "The prosecution must take all steps to prove its case. Any doubt should be read in favour of the Accused",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      175.93,
      390.55,
      189.21
    ],
    "text": "person. The owner of the benefit of the doubt is the Accused person.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      217.33,
      557.66,
      230.61
    ],
    "text": "Since the prosecution had failed to prove that a copy of the report was sent along with the charge sheet",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      238.09,
      558.14,
      251.37
    ],
    "text": "or that the Accused was given a copy before the 4th of January 2016, the Respondents had not complied",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      258.76,
      272.21,
      272.04
    ],
    "text": "with mandatory provisions of the Food Act.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      58.92,
      300.16,
      216.89,
      313.44
    ],
    "text": "Therefore, we allow the appeal.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      406.15,
      412.96,
